        "description": "We currently have code sprinkled around constructors that can technically fail because we either do a memcpy/allocation via vector copy constructor (we might be using a move constructor in places) and make_shared<>.\n\nThese are very small memory allocations but they can throw std::bad_alloc.\n\nTechnically, we would need to convert these to use Init or static factories.\n\n(types.h is one place to look)",
